commit.message:
[configtool] Include language name in im_dialog_filter

Input methods can be filtered from the language they target.

Until now, if you wanted to look for a specific input method
(i.e. "Pinyin" or "Mozc"), typing the language they target
("Chinese" or "Japanese" here) would not allow to find them.
You had to directly type the name of the input method.

This patch fixes this inconvenience by allowing to look for input
methods by the language they target.

NB: `gdm_get_language_from_name' may return NULL if the language
name is unknown. That's why a NULL check is necessary.
